datastructures.symbol_tables

Class BSTOrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.symbol_tables.ST<Key,Value>
      • datastructures.symbol_tables.OrderedST<Key,Value>
        • datastructures.symbol_tables.BSTOrderedST<Key,Value>
  • Type Parameters:
    Key - The Comparable type of key held by the symbol table.
    Value - The type of value mapped to by the key.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RBBSTOrderedST

    public class BSTOrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>
extends OrderedST<Key,Value>

    BSTOrderedST is a OrderedST implemented using a datastructures.trees.BinarySearchTree. The get() and put() operations are thus implemented in O(logN). This constitutes an improvement over DualArrayOrderedST, where every new insertion required shifting in the worst case N keys and N values to the right of the arrays contained within the object. A disadvantage is that other operations, such as min() and max(), which used to take constant time in that implementation, now take logarithmic time.

    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
